<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Comerica Earns $167 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Comerica Inc. said Thursday that second-quarter  
profits were up 11 percent to $167 million, due to more commercial 
lending and more profitable investments. 
</P>
<P>
	The state's largest bank said it earned $1.03 a share for the  
three months ending June 30, compared with $150 million, or 92 
cents a share, in the same period last year. For the first six 
months of 1999, Comerica earned $326 million, or $2.01 a share, up 
from $295 million, or $1.80 a share, last year. 
</P>
<P>
	The second quarter results were slightly higher than Wall Street  
expectations of $1.02 a share. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets totaled $37 billion for the quarter, up $2 billion from  
1998. Interest income for the quarter was $352 million, up $15 
million. Noninterest income was $195 million, compared to $149 
million for last year's quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Comerica had $31.1 billion in loans, an increase of $1 billion  
in the last six months, thanks to more business and construction 
loans and commercial mortgages. By contrast, residential mortgagees 
dropped 13 percent over the same period, and consumer loans were 
down 3 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Comerica has banking affiliates in Michigan, Texas, California  
and Florida. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
