game tonight in a gesture of respect to three workers who died when 
a huge crane collapsed while handling a portion of the roof for the 
team's new stadium. Five others were injured yesterday afternoon 
when the crane broke in half as it lifted the 400-ton load. The 
Brewers postponed their scheduled game against the Kansas City 
Royals. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by DAVID GOODMAN  




  	   	
