<DOCNO> APW19990715.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 11:40:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Advance; Dow Up 39.90 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks advanced today amid further evidence that  
the economy's surprising strength still hasn't sparked rapid 
inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	At 2 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow was up 39.90 at 11,188.00.  
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators held modest gains. The Nasdaq composite  
index was up 10.30 at 2,828.43 after rising nearly 40 points 
Wednesday to a new closing high. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index 
was up 10.15 at 1,408.32. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the start of trading, the Labor Department reported that  
consumer prices held steady in June for the second straight month -- 
the best showing since back in 1986, when prices actually fell 
three months in a row. 
</P>
<P>
	Economists had been expecting slight rise of 0.1 percent in the  
consumer price index. The data, along with Wednesday's news that 
prices at the wholesale level fell 0.1 percent in June, should help 
calm fears about an inflationary spurt back in April. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 9-to-7 ratio on the  
New York Stock Exchange, while Nasdaq gainers led by a slimmer 
margin. NYSE volume came to 366.07 million shares, up modestly from 
Wednesday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 5.08 at 659.98, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was up 1.99 at 814.99. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
