<HEADLINE> Doin' The Town Wins Sire Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Doin' The Town rallied down the  
stretch to win the $100,000 New Jersey Sire Stakes Final for 
2-year-old fillies Thursday night at the Meadowlands. 
</P>
<P>
	Doin' The Town, guided by Mike Lachance, caught Cumin's Promise  
down the stretch to win by 1 1/4 lengths in 1:59. Day For Night 
finished 3 1/4 lengths back for third. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't think I could beat that filly that made a break  
(Marita's Victory),'' Lachance said. ``She (Doin The Town) had her 
problems lately, but (trainer) Wayne (Nickells) has made some 
equipment changes. I qualified her back last week and she was good. 
Tonight, she was relaxed the whole way and she raced really easy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Doin' The Town, daughter of Donerail, posted her second win in  
four starts this year with earnings of $66,750. Doin The Town was 
purchased for $42,000 at the Harrisburg Yearling Sale. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was great,'' Nickells said. ``A couple weeks back we found  
that she had an abscess in her lower jaw and we switched her to an 
open bridle. That just turned her around. It has been like night 
and day. She is a nice filly who has a lot of ability.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Doin' The Town paid $19.40, $10.20, $5.60. Cumin's Promise paid  
$5.60 and $4.60, and Day For Night paid $4.80. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
