<HEADLINE> Ripken Hit by Pitch, Leaves Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Cal Ripken was hit by a pitch in the wrist  
Thursday night and removed from the Baltimore Orioles' game against 
the Montreal Expos. 
</P>
<P>
	Ripken was batting against Mike Thurman in the second inning  
when a pitch struck him on the right wrist. He winced in pain and 
trotted to first base, where he kicked the bag in disgust. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury was diagnosed as a bruise.  
</P>
<P>
	Ripken stayed in the game and scored a run, but was replaced at  
third base by Jeff Reboulet in the top of the third. 
</P>
<P>
	Such an incident might have drawn huge headlines a year ago,  
when Ripken was in the midst of his record streak of 2,632 
consecutive games. But he voluntarily ended that streak last 
September and earlier this year spent several weeks on the disabled 
list with back spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	Ripken also was hit by a pitch in the All-Star game Tuesday  
night. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
