<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Storm Wreck Wins at Hollywood Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Storm Wreck surged from last place and  
overtook even-money favorite Free to win Thursday's $53,972 feature 
at Hollywood Park by a half-length. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Alex Solis and carrying 116 pounds, Storm Wreck  
covered 1 1-16 miles in 1:42 and paid $7.40, $2.80 and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
	The third victory for Storm Wreck, a 4-year-old gelding, in 17  
career starts was worth $31,440, increasing his career earnings to 
$127,174. 
</P>
<P>
	Free, with Chris McCarron riding at 119 pounds, was unable to  
keep up with Storm Wreck's sustained rally and finished second, 
paying $2.80 and $2.60. March of Kings, a longshot with Garrett 
Gomez riding at 116 pounds, finished 5 1/2 lengths behind Free and 
paid $3.60 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
