<HEADLINE> Hawn, Russell Visit Poor Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LIMA, Peru (AP) -- Goldie Hawn and Kurt Russell visited a  
hospital in a Lima shantytown and played with impoverished children 
recovering from cleft palate surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hollywood couple spent Thursday at Maria Auxiliadora  
hospital as part of the LISTEN project in which artists, musicians 
and movie stars donate their time to help poor children. 
</P>
<P>
	Wearing green medical smocks and caps, they held children who  
had just had their palates surgically repaired for free as part of 
Operation Smile, a charity to help children with facial problems in 
the developing world. 
</P>
<P>
