<HEADLINE> Hawks Sign Glover to 3-Year Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Hawks on Thursday signed guard Dion  
Glover, one of the team's three first-round draft choices, to a 
three-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Under terms of the NBA rookie salary scale, Glover, the 20th  
overall pick in last month's draft, must be paid $744,500 the first 
year, $800,400 the second and $856,200 the third. Exact terms 
weren't revealed. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-5 Glover was the third-leading freshman scorer in the  
nation in 1997-98, averaging 18.4 points for Georgia Tech. 
</P>
<P>
	He missed last season after he tore left knee ligaments during  
his first practice as a sophomore. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hawks signed their other first-round choices, Jason Terry  
and Cal Bowdler, on Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
