<HEADLINE> Filmmaker Pleads Innocent in Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Academy Award-winning filmmaker  
Oliver Stone has pleaded innocent to drug charges stemming from a 
traffic stop last month. 
</P>
<P>
	Stone was stopped June 9 by a police officer who said the  
director was driving erratically. Police said they found hashish in 
his 1987 black Ford Mustang. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors said Stone's blood-alcohol level was above the legal  
limit of 0.08 percent when he was arrested. 
</P>
<P>
	Stone, 52, pleaded innocent Thursday to charges including of  
possession of controlled substances and driving under the 
influence. 
  	   	
</P>
