<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are have been moving substantially  
or trading heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq 
Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Ziff-Davis, up 4 1/16 at 18 1/4  
</P>
<P>
	The technology publisher, research firm and trade show organizer  
hired Morgan Stanley Dean Witter to explore strategic alternatives 
including alliances and mergers. Softbank of Japan, which is 
Ziff-Davis' majority owner, is refocusing its strategy on companies 
which operate totally on the Internet. 

</P>
<P>
	Timberland, up 13 15/16 at 78 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	The footwear and clothing maker reported a 26 percent jump in  
second-quarter profits citing an improvement in gross margins. 
Timberland, based in Stratham, N.H., also announced plans to buy 
back up to 1 million more common shares. 

</P>
<P>
	EnergyNorth, up 13 5/16 at 43  
</P>
<P>
	Eastern Enterprises is acquiring EnergyNorth for stock and cash  
worth $156 million, or $47 a share, plus assumed debt of $45.6 
million. EnergyNorth, based in Manchester, N.H., distributes 
natural gas in New Hampshire and Vermont, and provides 
mechanical-contracting services. Eastern, based in Weston, Mass. is 
the holding company for Boston Gas Co. and Midland Enterprises Inc. 

</P>
<P>
	ContiFinancial, down 2 5/16 at 1 5/8  
</P>
<P>
	Merger talks with Residential Funding Corp., a unit of General  
Motors, have ended. ContiFinancial said it is in talks with others 
regarding an acquisition or equity investment and has started talks 
with its lenders about its debt facilities. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
	Apple Computer, down 2 11/16 at 53 1/4  
</P>
<P>
	The stock pulled back after rallying on Wednesday before the  
computer maker's latest quarterly report, which easily surpassed 
most Wall Street forecasts. Apple's profit nearly doubled in its 
third quarter ended June 26 as demand surged for iMac desktop PCs. 

</P>
<P>
	Viasoft, up 2 1/4 at 8 19/32  
</P>
<P>
	Compuware agreed to pay $9 a share to acquire the Phoenix-based  
provider of information technology management. Compuware, based in 
Farmington Hills, Mich., is a provider of management and 
development software. 

</P>
<P>
	Cumetrix Data Systems, down 5/8 at 2 5/16  
</P>
<P>
	The supplier of computer-related products is trying to prevent  
being delisted by the Nasdaq Stock Exchange, which will hold a 
hearing on the matter. Cumetrix, based in Industry, Calif. didn't 
file its annual 10-K report on time, and its stock symbol has been 
changed from CDSC to CDSCE, a step toward being delisted. 

</P>
<P>
	Kevco, up 1/8 at 7 1/8  
</P>
<P>
	Wingate Partners II LP agreed to buy $37 million worth of  
shares, convertible debt and warrants from the maker of building 
products for housing and recreational vehicles. Assuming full 
exercise of all convertible securities, Wingate would own about 46 
percent of the voting shares in the Fort Worth, Texas, company 

</P>
<P>
	Audiohighway.com, up 3 1/8 at 24 1/4  
</P>
<P>
	The company will pilot an audio books channel on Microsoft's  
WindowsMedia.com. Links on the WindowsMedia.com home page will 
direct users to access free audio books from Audiohighway.com, 
which is based in Cupertino, Calif. 


  	   	
</P>
