<HEADLINE> AP Corrects New Element Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	In a July 14 story about the discovery of a new element, The  
Associated Press incorrectly reported that the element has an 
atomic weight of 114. The element's atomic number is 114, meaning 
it has 114 protons in its nucleus. The atomic weight varies with 
the number of neutrons the element has. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
