<HEADLINE> D-Backs' Johnson Gets Some Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- For the first time in 34 innings, the  
Arizona Diamondbacks scored a run for Randy Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson took a 1-0 lead to the mound Thursday night after Matt  
Williams singled to left with two out in the top of the first, 
driving in Tony Womack. The 1,500th hit of Williams' career ensured 
that Johnson wouldn't be shut out for a fifth straight start. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson is the 10th player since 1900 to lose four straight  
games while his team was shut out each time, according to the Elias 
Sports Bureau, baseball's statistician. Johnson gave up just five 
earned runs over those 32 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	The drought began in the last two innings five starts ago on  
June 20, also a Johnson loss. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
