<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 14:00:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boy, 14, Sentenced to Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSON, Mich. (AP) -- A 14-year-old boy was sentenced to life in  
prison Thursday for murdering a classmate by stabbing her 33 times. 
</P>
<P>
	Martez Stewart will be eligible for parole in 15 years. He was  
convicted in May in the slaying of 14-year-old Stacy Davis. 
</P>
<P>
	Police never established a motive, but the girl's parents said  
Stewart had been banned from the house after pushing Stacy's 
younger brother. Acquaintances said Stacy had rebuffed Stewart's 
advances. 
</P>
<P>
	Stewart was 13 at the time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
