<HEADLINE> Energy Secretary's Beard Temporary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Energy Secretary Bill Richardson was  
introduced Thursday by his deputy as a man with ``a new look and a 
sense of action.'' Maybe the beard had something to do with it. 
</P>
<P>
	Richardson said his new beard, grown during a recent week-long  
vacation on Cape Cod, probably won't be permanent. For one thing 
his wife, Barbara, is not crazy about it. 
</P>
<P>
	``She's not being very supportive or helpful,'' he confided.  
</P>
<P>
	Richardson for months has been the point man in containing the  
nuclear weapons espionage controversy for the administration, and 
he thought growing a beard might bring him some new fortune. 
</P>
<P>
	``I went on vacation and decided not to shave. I looked at  
myself in the mirror and I felt I needed some better luck,'' he 
said. ``I liked the look. It saves me 70 minutes a week in not 
shaving. So, I've grown the beard, but it's not permanent.'' 
  	   	
</P>
