<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Activate Arrojo and Yan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Right-handers Rolando Arrojo and  
Esteban Yan were activated from the disabled list Thursday by the 
Tampa Bay Devil Rays, who designated reliever Julio Santana for 
assignment. 
</P>
<P>
	Arrojo, sidelined since May 26 because of shoulder inflammation,  
made his first start in nearly seven weeks against the New York 
Mets on Thursday night. Yan, who returned to the bullpen, had been 
out since June 20 with a sore right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Santana (1-4, 7.32 ERA) must be traded, sent outright to the  
minors or released within 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
	The other roster opened when Jose Canseco, who leads the AL with  
31 homers, was placed on the disabled list Sunday after back 
surgery last Sunday. He is expected to be sidelined for about six 
weeks. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
