<HEADLINE> Calif. Teen Opens Meet With Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Kaitlin Sandeno of Mission Viejo, Calif., won  
the women's 800-meter freestyle Thursday, the opening event of the 
Janet Evans Invitational at USC. 
</P>
<P>
	Sandeno, 16, won her first national title this spring in the  
400-meter individual medley and continued a strong showing Thursday 
by finishing first in 8 minutes, 36.21 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm really happy with the race,'' said Sandeno, who is  
scheduled to swim in 10 events during the four-day meet. ``I wanted 
to go under 8:40 and I did. It's not too far off my best time, so 
I'm happy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ryk Neethling of South Africa also beat his own meet record  
Thursday in winning the men's 800 in 8:01.36, improving his old 
mark by close to 6 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was surprised, I didn't think I was going that fast,''  
Neethling said. 
</P>
<P>
	Chad Carvin of Mission Viejo finished second in 8:07.28.  
</P>
<P>
	The invitational, which has more than 700 competitors, is the  
last major meet before the U.S. Summer National Championships. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
