<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Fair skies prevailed Thursday in the nation's midsection, with  
scattered showers in the Southeast and thunderstorms in the West. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers dampened the Outer Banks of North Carolina and parts of  
Tennessee and Georgia. Thunderstorms struck parts of Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	A ridge of high pressure brought fair and hot weather to the  
Great Lakes region through the Ohio and Tennessee valleys into the 
Mississippi Valley and the Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers and storms were widespread from North Dakota to the  
Rockies. Portions of Arizona, including Phoenix, also received 
storms. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair to partly cloudy skies and dry weather continued in the  
Pacific Northwest. 
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the lower 48 states was 94 degrees in Palm  
Springs, Calif. The low was 30 in Stanley, Idaho. 
  	   	
</P>
