<HEADLINE> NL Wins Double A All Star Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- John Curl, representing the hometown Mobile  
Baybears, hit a three-run home run in the seventh inning Wednesday 
night as the National League beat the American League 3-0 in the 
Double-A All-Star Game. 
</P>
<P>
	Curl's shot over the wall in right center came after Reading's  
Pat Burrell singled to left field and Greenville's Steve Goodell 
walked. Curl homered off the AL's Trevor Enders of Orlando with one 
out. 
</P>
