<HEADLINE> Unisys Profits Rise 33 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BLUE BELL, Pa. (AP) -- Strong growth in computer services led  
Unisys Corp. to a 33 percent increase in second-quarter profit, 
easily surpassing Wall Street predictions. 
</P>
<P>
	Unisys reported Thursday it earned $119.7 million, or 38 cents  
per share, during the three months ended June 30. That was up from 
a profit of $90.1 million, or 24 cents per share, during the same 
period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Revenue grew 9 percent to $1.89 billion from $1.73 billion.  
</P>
<P>
	The Blue Bell, Pa.-based computer manufacturing and services  
company cited double-digit increases in revenue, including big 
gains in the United States, Europe and Asia. 
</P>
<P>
	Unisys also saw a 3 percent growth in computer technology  
revenue, partly due to continued strong shipments of business 
computers called servers, which run networks of smaller machines. 
</P>
<P>
	The profit exceeded the 33 cents per share expected by analysts  
surveyed by First Call. Unisys stock rose 37 1/2 cents at $44.43 3/4 in 
trading on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Net income for the first six months of the year was $230.9  
million, or 70 cents per share, on revenue of $3.7 billion. That 
was up from a profit of $152.8 million, or 38 cents per share, on 
revenue of $3.38 billion in the first six months of 1998. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
