<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Both Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar fell against other major currencies in  
European trading today. Gold also fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0244 in late European trading up from  
$1.0174 Wednesday. Later in midday trading in New York, the euro 
traded at $1.0221. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday,  
included 120.41 Japanese yen, down from 120.69; 1.5658 Swiss 
francs, down from 1.5759; and 1.4792 Canadian dollars, down from 
1.4804. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5686, up from $1.5595.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 120.42 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.5635. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.9092 German marks, down from 1.9224; 
6.4033 French francs, down from 6.4474; 2.1512 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.1660; and 1890.15 Italian lire, down from 1,903.16. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $253.50 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$254.70 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $253.05, down from $254.75.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $1.70 in Hong Kong to close at $253.95.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.05 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.11. 
  	   	
</P>
