<HEADLINE> Argentina's Jobless Rate Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) -- Argentina's unemployment rate  
rose to 14.5 percent in May, up from 12.4 percent at last reading 
in October, according to government figures published today. 
</P>
<P>
	Rising unemployment comes amid a deepening recession in  
Argentina and means some 1.8 million of the workforce are without 
jobs. In May 1998, the nation's unemployment rate stood at 13.2 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	A separate measure of underemployment also inched up to 13.7  
percent in May from 13.6 percent in October, according to the 
national statistics institute. Underemployment is defined as those 
working less than 35 hours a week who want to be employed fulltime. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
