<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cardinals Sign First-Round Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Right-hander Chance Caple, the St. Louis  
Cardinals' first pick in last month's amateur draft, agreed 
Thursday to a minor league contract with a $1.2 million signing 
bonus. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's unbelievable, and I hope to be here soon,'' he said after  
walking onto the field at Busch Stadium. ``I'm looking forward to 
the challenge.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Caple, 20, was the 30th pick overall after going 8-5 with 125  
strikeouts in 114 innings as a junior for Texas A&AMP;M. 
</P>
<P>
	He's another promising arm in the Cardinals' system, which  
includes left-hander Rick Ankiel, who got a $2.5 million bonus in 
1997 and is now at Triple-A Memphis, and right-hander Chad 
Hutchinson, who a $3.5 million, four-year deal and is at Double-A 
Arkansas. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've heard a lot about them,'' Caple said. ``I've just tried  
to put myself in a position where I can be successful.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The process starts Friday when he heads for New Jersey of the  
Class A New York-Penn League. A plus is the Cardinals also drafted 
and signed his college catcher, eighth-rounder Shawn Schumacher, 
and he's already playing at New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	``He loves it, and he's looking forward to it,'' Caple said.  
``This makes it easier to adjust.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
