<HEADLINE> Mariners' New Ballpark Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Safe opened for business Thursday, with the  
Seattle Mariners uncertain whether they can keep Ken Griffey Jr. 
and Alex Rodriguez locked up. 
</P>
<P>
	After 22 1/2 seasons in the climate-controlled Kingdome, the  
