<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-firemen Charged in Deadly Arson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Seven current or former firefighters  
tried to impress their chief by setting fire to a house and then 
putting out the blaze, but one got trapped inside and was killed, 
investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
	The six other men were arrested Thursday on charges of  
conspiracy, arson and burglary and could get up to 87 years in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
	The man who died, Daniel Neil Hixson, was a former firefighter.  
Hixson had left the department when he moved out of the area, then 
came back last month, hoping to return to duty. 
</P>
<P>
	His six colleagues apparently thought that if the chief saw him  
fighting a fire, it would help win back his job, Sheriff John Cupp 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hixson, 26, poured gasoline inside the home June 26, then became  
trapped by smoke and flames and died, Cupp said. 
</P>
<P>
	The owner of the house was not home. The back of the house was  
heavily damaged. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
