 *A gift of land to save a soul    	
</P>
<P>
	YANKTON, S.D. (AP) -- A man who lost a son to acute alcoholism is  
giving $213,000 in land to a church he doesn't attend. The Rev. 
Jeff Mantz said the First Assembly of God would build a larger 
church on the site. 
</P>
<P>
	Mantz said he and other church members had approached the man  
with the idea of buying some of his land in a growing part of town. 
</P>
<P>
	``We sat down for the first 15 minutes, and we answered his  
questions about our need for land,'' Mantz said. ``The rest of the 
time, he asked about our vision and plans.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When the delegation asked to buy, the landowner said he'd  
donate. 
</P>
<P>
	``The couple had a son who died of acute alcoholism. The man  
said, 'If you can help to win one back from the edge, I will be 
more than repaid,''' Mantz said. 
</P>
<P>
	The church, with a sanctuary for 350 people, is expected to be  
completed next summer. 
</P>
