<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 63; Nasdaq Climbs 12 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 63 points  
in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange 
hold a two-to-one lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 12 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up eight points. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts expected stocks would open higher, helped along by  
positive earnings reports and good news on the inflation front. 
</P>
<P>
	Technology issues are expected to move up from yesterday's  
record close. 
</P>
<P>
	But analysts say the tech stocks have been troubled by the same  
problems faced by the broader market. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors have already factored strong second-quarter profits  
into stock prices, and the release of the quarterly numbers has 
prompted some profit-taking. 
  	   	
</P>
