<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-15 13:10:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dodgers, Marlins Complete Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- The Florida Marlins acquired left-hander Ryan  
Moskau on Thursday as the player to be named in the deal that sent 
infielder Craig Counsell to the Los Angeles Dodgers last month. 
</P>
<P>
	Moskau was 5-5 with a 4.15 ERA in 17 starts this year for Class  
A Vero Beach. His contract was assigned to Class A Brevard County. 
</P>
<P>
	Moskau, 21, is the son of former major league pitcher Paul  
Moskau. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
